  1→# Type definitions for coding agent CLIs in SDK mode
  2→
  3→Four major coding agent CLIs now offer programmatic access through TypeScript SDKs with well-defined type systems. **OpenCode provides the most complete formal specification** with a published OpenAPI 3.1.1 schema, while Claude Code and Codex offer comprehensive TypeScript types through npm packages. All four tools use similar patterns: streaming events via JSON lines, discriminated union types for messages, and structured configuration schemas.
  4→
  5→## Codex CLI has TypeScript SDK but no formal schema
  6→
  7→OpenAI's Codex CLI provides programmatic control through the **`@openai/codex-sdk`** package, which wraps the bundled binary and exchanges JSONL events over stdin/stdout. Types are well-defined in source code but not published as JSON Schema or OpenAPI specifications.
  8→
  9→**Core SDK types from `@openai/codex-sdk`:**
 10→
 11→```typescript
 12→interface CodexOptions {
 13→  codexPathOverride?: string;
 14→  baseURL?: string;
 15→  apiKey?: string;
 16→  env?: Record<string, string>;
 17→}
 18→
 19→interface ThreadOptions {
 20→  model?: string;
 21→  sandboxMode?: "read-only" | "workspace-write" | "danger-full-access";
 22→  workingDirectory?: string;
 23→  skipGitRepoCheck?: boolean;
 24→}
 25→
 26→interface TurnOptions {
 27→  outputSchema?: Record<string, unknown>;  // JSON Schema for structured output
 28→}
 29→
 30→type Input = string | UserInput[];
 31→interface UserInput {
 32→  type: "text" | "local_image";
 33→  text?: string;
 34→  path?: string;
 35→}
 36→```
 37→
 38→**Event types for streaming (`runStreamed()`):**
 39→
 40→```typescript
 41→type EventType = "thread.started" | "turn.started" | "turn.completed" | 
 42→                 "turn.failed" | "item.started" | "item.updated" | 
 43→                 "item.completed" | "error";
 44→
 45→interface ThreadEvent {
 46→  type: EventType;
 47→  thread_id?: string;
 48→  usage?: { input_tokens: number; cached_input_tokens: number; output_tokens: number };
 49→  error?: { message: string };
 50→  item?: ThreadItem;
 51→}
 52→
 53→type ItemType = "agent_message" | "reasoning" | "command_execution" | 
 54→                "file_change" | "mcp_tool_call" | "web_search" | 
 55→                "todo_list" | "error" | "unknown";
 56→```
 57→
 58→**Key source files:** `sdk/typescript/src/` contains `items.ts`, `events.ts`, `options.ts`, `input.ts`, and `thread.ts`. Documentation at https://developers.openai.com/codex/sdk/ and https://developers.openai.com/codex/noninteractive/.
